@startuml event-flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

title Event Recording & Rendering Flow

actor User
participant "Keyboard /\nButton" as Input
participant "processKeySequence()" as PKS
participant "recordEvent()" as REC
participant "appState.events[]" as LOG
participant "getEffectiveBoutEvents()" as EFF
participant "calculateScores()" as CALC
participant "updateTimeline()" as TL
participant "DOM" as DOM

User -> Input : Press key / Click btn
Input -> PKS : key sequence
PKS -> REC : {eventType, boutTime100ms}

REC -> LOG : push({seq, timestamp, ...})
REC -> CALC : updateScores()
CALC -> EFF : get events
EFF -> LOG : read raw events
EFF -> EFF : apply corrections\n(EventModified,\nEventDeleted,\nEventInserted,\nEventSwapped)
EFF --> CALC : effective events[]
CALC --> DOM : scoreRedDisplay\nscoreBlueDisplay

REC -> TL : updateTimeline()
TL -> EFF : get events
EFF --> TL : effective events[]
TL -> TL : iterate & create\nDOM elements
TL --> DOM : timeline.innerHTML

note over EFF
  **getEffectiveBoutEvents()** is called
  multiple times per cycle:
  - updateScores() → calculateScores()
  - updateTimeline()
  - autoUpdateCompletionForm()
  Each call re-filters the full event log
  and re-applies all corrections.
end note

@enduml
